CGC Canopy Growth Corp said on Wednesday it would buy skincare company This Works for 552 million USD adding beauty and sleep products to the Canadian weed producers portfolio of cannabis oil hemp and medical capsulesLondonbased This Works set up in 2003 by a former beauty director of Vogue UK and yoga teacher makes pillow sprays that help users sleep faster moisturisers to reduce wrinkles body oils and eyecare products according to its websiteCanopy Growth said the acquisition fits with its strategy of expanding internationally and would help develop CBDinfused products and brands for the global beauty and wellness spaceLVMHs Sephora beauty chain has been selling CBDinfused products since 2018 Jefferies expects the CBD beauty market to reach 25 billion in 10 years accounting for 1015 of global skincare salesSome Hollywood celebrities including Jennifer Aniston Mandy Moore and Olivia Wilde have also backed CBDinfused products in media interviews
